===Glyph origin===
First attested as the phonetic component of {{zh-l|*жҶҗ}} in stone carvings in a form ancestral to the small seal script. In the small seal script, {{zh-l|*иҲӣ}} is graphically detached from the {{zh-l|*еӨ§}} with the dots, which in turn is split vertically and interpreted as the unrelated {{zh-l|*зӮҺ}}; ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously interprets it as an {{Han compound|зӮҺ|иҲӣ|ls=ic|t1=fire; flame|t2=feet|nocap=1}}.<ref>йҷіж–Ҝйө¬пјҡгҖҠиҲҠйҮӢвҖңзІҰвҖқеӯ—еҸҠзӣёй—ңе•ҸйЎҢж–°и§ЈгҖӢпјҢгҖҠж–ҮеҸІгҖӢ2019е№ҙз¬¬4ијҜпјҢз¬¬5вҖ”18й ҒгҖӮ</ref> In the regular script, the top further corrupts into the unrelated {{zh-l|*зұі}}.
